    <p>If the columns balance in the Grey's favour for your home, the last variable is the bird's origin. A documented, captive-bred African Grey converts every risk on the con side — health, legality, temperament — into paperwork you can hold.</p>
    <h3 class="cag-h3">How Health Documentation Removes the Nastiest Surprises</h3>
    <p>Once the pros win, the way to avoid the cons' worst edge is documentation. A Grey that arrives with CITES paperwork, DNA sexing, PBFD and Avian Polyomavirus PCR results and an avian-vet certificate is a bird whose health and legality you never have to wonder about — the standard behind our written <a href="/african-grey-parrot-health-guarantee/">health guarantee</a> and every Congo on the <a href="/congo-african-grey-for-sale/">Congo African Grey page</a> and Timneh on the <a href="/timneh-african-grey-for-sale/">Timneh page</a>. Choosing a documented bird from a reputable, USDA-licensed breeder is the single decision that turns the risk column from a gamble into a known quantity.</p>
  </section>

